#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:41
msgid "Colors"
msgstr "Cores"

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:43
msgid ""
"Odoo's website editor features two main types of colors: :ref:`theme colors "
"<website/themes/theme-colors>` and :ref:`status colors <website/themes/"
"status-colors>`."
msgstr ""
"O editor de sites do Odoo possui dois tipos principais de cores: :ref:`cores "
"do tema <website/themes/theme-colors>` e :ref:`cores de status <website/"
"themes/status-colors>`."

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:49
msgid "Theme colors"
msgstr "Cores do tema"

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:51
msgid ""
"Theme colors refer to the set of colors displayed across all pages of the "
"website. They consist of five colors: three :guilabel:`Main` colors, used "
"mainly for buttons and links, and two :guilabel:`Light & Dark` colors, used "
"mainly for text and headings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:55
msgid ""
"To edit the website's colors, navigate to the :guilabel:`Colors` section of "
"the :guilabel:`Theme` tab. Then:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:58
msgid ""
"Click the color you want to change, then select a "
"predefined :guilabel:`Solid` color or click :guilabel:`Custom` to pick a "
"specific color tone manually (or add its #HEX or RGBA code). Click :icon:`fa-"
"trash` (:guilabel:`Reset`) to remove the color selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:61
msgid ""
"Click the paint palette icon and choose a color palette. As a result, all "
"color customizations are reset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:64
msgid ""
"Odoo automatically creates :guilabel:`Color Presets` for the chosen colors "
"or palette. These predefined color combinations are applied to various "
"elements of the website to create a structured and visually appealing "
"design. When selecting a color palette, its presets define how those colors "
"are distributed across different elements. To modify them, "
"click :guilabel:`Color Presets`, then select a preset to open the "
"customization dropdown. Each color preset contains colors for the building "
"block’s :guilabel:`Background`, :guilabel:`Text`, :guilabel:`Headings`, :guilabel:`Links`, :guilabel:`Primary "
"Buttons`, and :guilabel:`Secondary Buttons`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:73
msgid ""
"To apply a color preset to a building block, select the building block, go "
"to the :guilabel:`Style` tab, click the color dot located next "
"to :guilabel:`Background`, and choose a :guilabel:`Theme`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:78
msgid ""
"Changing a color preset automatically updates the colors of both the default "
"preset and the building blocks that use it."
msgstr ""
"Alterar uma predefinição de cor atualiza automaticamente as cores tanto da "
"predefinição padrão quanto dos blocos de construção que a utilizam."

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:84
msgid "Status colors"
msgstr "Cores de status"

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:86
msgid ""
"Status colors indicate the status of certain actions "
"(e.g., :guilabel:`Success`, :guilabel:`Warning`, etc.). They're used in pop-"
"up messages that appear to provide feedback to users and website visitors. "
"To customize the website's :guilabel:`Status Colors`, scroll down to "
"the :ref:`Advanced <website/themes/advanced>` section and click the dots to "
"change their color."
msgstr ""
"As cores de status indicam o status de determinadas ações (por "
"exemplo, :guilabel:`Sucesso`, :guilabel:`Aviso`, etc.). Elas são usadas em "
"mensagens pop-up que aparecem para fornecer feedback aos usuários e "
"visitantes do site. Para personalizar as :guilabel:`Cores de Status` do "
"site, role para baixo até a seção :ref:`Avançado <website/themes/advanced>` "
"e clique nos pontos para alterar sua cor."

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:93
msgid ""
"Information related to a successful action on the website appears "
"in :icon:`oi-green-dot` green."
msgstr ""
"Informações relacionadas a uma ação bem-sucedida no site aparecem "
"em :icon:`oi-green-dot` verde."

#: ../../content/applications/websites/website/web_design/themes.rst:0
